The image presents a graph with two lines, one labeled "Power-on Glitch" and the other labeled "Reset-to-mid Scale". The graph displays voltage values for both the power-on glitch and the mid-scale settings of a device. The x-axis represents time in seconds, while the y-axis represents voltage in volts.

The graph shows that the device operates at a higher voltage during the power-on glitch setting compared to the mid-scale setting. This information can be useful for understanding how the device performs under different conditions and may help troubleshoot any issues related to its operation.
